Hello Taylor and all,

Interesting subject! I've heard that shipwrecks often provide insights into ancient trade routes. Artifacts recovered can tell us about cultures and economies of the past. The level of preservation depends on the conditions around the wreck.

Also, the effort to conserve these finds so the public can learn from them is commendable. These wrecks are as much about our history as they are about discovery.

Do you find this aspect of preservation as captivating as I do?

Best,
